title: Troll Talking Interceptor (ADR-228 Phase 5 + ADR-229 R4)
story: dungeo
description: TrollTalkingInterceptor owns the full talk-to-troll canon through
  stdlib if.action.talking — GROWLS override while the troll is conscious
  (postReport, ADR-229 R4), the MDL "can't hear you" veto when KO'd. The
  bespoke talk_to_troll action is deleted; all phrasings ride the core talk
  patterns (ADR-229 R3) plus the story's `hello :target`. The conscious-troll
  check runs FIRST and briefly (troll combat RNG — one-good-run rule).

---

# Setup — lantern + teleport in one GDT session (no turns pass inside GDT)
> GDT
[OK: contains "GDT"]

> TK brass lantern
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> AH Troll Room
[OK: contains "Teleported"]

> EX
[OK: contains "Returning"]

> turn on lantern
[OK: contains "on"]

# ============================================================
# Conscious troll: postReport override — GROWLS canon, not the
# stdlib greeting (ADR-229 R4). Core R3 pattern carries it.
# ============================================================

> talk to troll
[OK: contains "growls menacingly"]

# ============================================================
# KO the troll, then the preValidate veto renders the MDL line
# ============================================================

> GDT
[OK: contains "GDT"]

> KO troll
[OK: contains "Knocked out"]

> EX
[OK: contains "Returning"]

# Core R3 pattern (speak to)
> speak to troll
[OK: contains "can't hear you"]

# Core R3 pattern (talk to) — previously a bespoke-action literal
> talk to troll
[OK: contains "can't hear you"]

# Story `hello :target` slot pattern (replaces the old literal)
> hello troll
[OK: contains "can't hear you"]
